#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an9.72"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.72:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.72:0.2"
msgid "7. Satipaṭṭhānavagga "
msgstr "7. Mindfulness Meditation "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 72. Cetasovinibandhasutta → vinibandhasatipaṭṭhānasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.72:0.3"
msgid "72. Cetasovinibandhasutta "
msgstr "72. Emotional Shackles "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.461, sc1
#. VAR: cetasovinibandhā → cetovinibaddhā (sāratthadīpanīṭīkā)
msgctxt "an9.72:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, cetasovinibandhā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five emotional shackles. "

msgctxt "an9.72:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an9.72:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāmesu avītarāgo hoti avigatacchando avigatapemo avigatapipāso avigatapariḷāho avigatataṇho. "
msgstr "Firstly, a mendicant isn’t free of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "an9.72:1.4"
msgid "Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāmesu avītarāgo hoti avigatacchando avigatapemo avigatapipāso avigatapariḷāho avigatataṇho, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya. "
msgstr "This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving. "

msgctxt "an9.72:1.5"
msgid "Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, ayaṃ paṭhamo cetasovinibandho. "
msgstr "This is the first emotional shackle. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an9.72:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye avītarāgo hoti … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant isn’t free of greed for the body … "

msgctxt "an9.72:2.2"
msgid "rūpe avītarāgo hoti … "
msgstr "They’re not free of greed for form … "

msgctxt "an9.72:2.3"
msgid "yāvadatthaṃ udarāvadehakaṃ bhuñjitvā seyyasukhaṃ passasukhaṃ middhasukhaṃ anuyutto viharati … "
msgstr "They eat as much as they like until their belly is full, then indulge in the pleasures of sleeping, lying, and drowsing … "

msgctxt "an9.72:2.4"
msgid "aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ paṇidhāya brahmacariyaṃ carati: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti. "
msgstr "They live the spiritual life wishing to be reborn in one of the orders of gods: ‘By this precept or observance or mortification or spiritual life, may I become one of the gods!’ "

msgctxt "an9.72:2.5"
msgid "Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ paṇidhāya brahmacariyaṃ carati: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya. "
msgstr "This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving. "

msgctxt "an9.72:2.6"
msgid "Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, ayaṃ pañcamo cetasovinibandho. "
msgstr "This is the fifth emotional shackle. "

msgctxt "an9.72:2.7"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca cetasovinibandhā. "
msgstr "These are the five emotional shackles. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an9.72:3.1"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ cetasovinibandhānaṃ pahānāya cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvetabbā. "
msgstr "To give up these five emotional shackles you should develop the four kinds of mindfulness meditation. "

msgctxt "an9.72:3.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an9.72:3.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "an9.72:3.4"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "an9.72:3.5"
msgid "citte … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the mind … "

msgctxt "an9.72:3.6"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "an9.72:3.7"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ cetasovinibandhānaṃ pahānāya ime cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvetabbā”ti. "
msgstr "To give up these five emotional shackles you should develop these four kinds of mindfulness meditation.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.72:3.8"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.72:3.9"
msgid "Satipaṭṭhānavaggo dutiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.462, sc4
msgctxt "an9.72:4.1"
msgid "Sikkhā nīvaraṇākāmā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an9.72:4.2"
msgid "Khandhā ca orambhāgiyā gati; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an9.72:4.3"
msgid "Maccheraṃ uddhambhāgiyā aṭṭhamaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an9.72:4.4"
msgid "Cetokhilā vinibandhāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
